Lifecycle Methods


1. Mounting Phase 

a. We have certain functions ( this is also considered the baby phase) 

b. Constructor()

c. Render()

d. ComponentDidMount()  => "Dom Content Loaded " 

componentWIllMount .. depricated

componentWillUpdate ... depricated 


2. Updating Phase 

a. shouldComponentUpdate() ==> which must return a boolean if this does not return a boolean you'll get a warning or react will yell at you and WILL not continue with your update

b. render()

c. componentDidUpdate >> DO NOT USE WILL UPDATE == Depricated


3. Unmounting Phase 

a. componentWillUnmount() 

4. Error Handling Phase     
